Usually this is caused by a later version of the compiler attempting to process
a library built with an earlier version of the compiler (or vice versa).  We
guarantee compatibility between some levels of the compiler (1.2.1 > 1.5) but
only when AspectJ5 is finished.  Until then we aren't going to guarantee
compatibility between milestone releases or dev releases.  Worst case, this
means full rebuilds of all your code until we are finished, each time you grab a
dev build.
*** Bug 99623 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

everything. All my other projects compile and work except this one. I will try 
to find what triggers this but it looks quite hard without compiling a logging 
compiler. (The file printed has probably not much to do with the error)

Unfortunately we've reached some 1.5 dependency that prevents me from compiling 
this project with the 1.2 compiler which can successfully compile it...
